1939;;The Magnificent Fraud;;American;;Robert Florey;;Akim Tamiroff, Patricia Morison;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Magnificent_Fraud;;Akim Tamiroff plays an actor performing in a nameless Latin American country who is pressed into service when the president is fatally injured by a bomb. Impersonating the president, the actor balances the pleasures and temptations of office, dangerous palace intrigue, and his duty to the people of the country.<br><br>The plot is identical to the 1988 Richard Dreyfuss film Moon over Parador; both are based on a short story by Charles G. Booth called Caviar for His Excellency.<br><br>Parts of the film were shot in Balboa Park in San Diego.